1
00:00:00,420 --> 00:00:02,746
It was really crazy last week.

2
00:00:02,771 --> 00:00:09,569
Firstly, the participants are full of
charms and distinct personalities.

3
00:00:10,327 --> 00:00:13,200
Also, there was a new rule.
It was refreshingly new.

4
00:00:13,225 --> 00:00:18,806
And there was a bit of
a spoiler of the final, too.

5
00:00:19,971 --> 00:00:22,048
I think he was interested in you.
I'm sure he was.

6
00:00:22,872 --> 00:00:24,331
That's how I felt.

7
00:00:24,808 --> 00:00:26,541
But you know you were selfish, too.

8
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:33,267
I actually trusted Su-won, but
I think I should be wary of him.

9
00:00:33,292 --> 00:00:35,406
Right. She mentioned he was selfish.

10
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:40,092
Some of the Money Catchers
are lying about their identities.

11
00:00:40,117 --> 00:00:41,802
That was a new rule.

12
00:00:41,827 --> 00:00:45,265
That means someone is nonchalantly lying.

13
00:00:45,452 --> 00:00:50,651
- If Jae-hyung is lying, then
he should go into acting. - I agree.

14
00:00:50,676 --> 00:00:53,410
It's method acting. Seriously.

15
00:00:53,435 --> 00:00:57,334
So, every week, we'll be
given a problem to solve.

16
00:00:57,814 --> 00:01:00,744
If you get it right, you'll
be given a Love Coin.

17
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:06,119
Those with the most Love
Coins will get a gold coin.

18
00:01:07,411 --> 00:01:08,878
Are you all confident?

19
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:16,600
(Who is the Money Catcher who
has lied about their information?)

20
00:01:16,625 --> 00:01:17,952
This is the question?

21
00:01:17,977 --> 00:01:21,160
So the one with the fake information
is the Money Catcher, right?

22
00:01:21,185 --> 00:01:25,125
- Precisely. They're the Money Catcher.
- Then they're telling us that already?

23
00:01:25,264 --> 00:01:26,843
Is this the last episode?

24
00:01:28,025 --> 00:01:30,520
- It's only episode 2.
- We didn't have a chance to get close.

25
00:01:30,545 --> 00:01:32,364
Will they tell us the answer right away?

26
00:01:32,389 --> 00:01:35,946
Right. They'll give us the answer
before today's episode ends.

27
00:01:37,191 --> 00:01:40,260
(Love Mansion, a place where
you can experience nature in Seoul)

28
00:01:41,455 --> 00:01:44,504
I love how there's a forest.
It's so wonderful.

29
00:01:45,578 --> 00:01:47,483
- Should we go?
- Do we go over there?

30
00:01:48,582 --> 00:01:49,764
It's here!

31
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:52,679
- Wow!
- Whoa, it's nice.

32
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:55,062
Oh, so they have separate places.

33
00:01:55,366 --> 00:01:56,366
It's great!

34
00:01:57,477 --> 00:01:59,064
- Oh my god.
- Wow!

35
00:01:59,484 --> 00:02:02,394
- It's beautiful!
- Amazing!

36
00:02:03,598 --> 00:02:05,582
- It's so lovely.
- Perfect!

37
00:02:06,068 --> 00:02:09,219
- It's awesome. - I can't believe
there's a place like this in Seoul.

38
00:02:09,244 --> 00:02:10,937
Wow, it's fantastic!

39
00:02:12,194 --> 00:02:13,194
It's great.

40
00:02:13,764 --> 00:02:15,662
I didn't know it would be so spacious.

41
00:02:18,201 --> 00:02:19,334
Wow, what's this?

42
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:22,908
Did you check this out?

43
00:02:23,666 --> 00:02:25,285
- Wow.
- Wow, this is awesome!

44
00:02:26,034 --> 00:02:28,423
- It's a hot springs.
- This is legendary.

45
00:02:28,918 --> 00:02:31,648
- Wonderful.
- Why is it so nice?

46
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:35,350
Wow, it's great. But the beds...

47
00:02:36,116 --> 00:02:37,672
- Is there another bed?
- No.

48
00:02:38,356 --> 00:02:40,181
- Wow.
- That's all you thought about, huh?

49
00:02:40,206 --> 00:02:41,763
Yes, I kept thinking about it.

50
00:02:42,178 --> 00:02:44,671
- She's overjoyed.
- She's so happy. She even danced.

51
00:02:44,696 --> 00:02:46,259
Then are there really just four women?

52
00:02:46,284 --> 00:02:50,476
- Is there an extra bed somewhere?
- Isn't there plenty of space for one?

53
00:02:50,702 --> 00:02:54,815
Maybe someone will come
with an electric blanket.

54
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:56,151
"Hello."

55
00:02:56,953 --> 00:02:58,086
That's hilarious.

56
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,767
Our beds... The older
ones can sleep here...

57
00:03:01,187 --> 00:03:02,379
Older ones vs. younger ones.

58
00:03:02,404 --> 00:03:04,318
What? It's not like we're dating.

59
00:03:04,343 --> 00:03:06,365
We'll end up in a bromance.

60
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:08,544
- I think it's great.
- So like this?

61
00:03:08,569 --> 00:03:09,951
- Yes.
- Okay.

62
00:03:09,976 --> 00:03:11,160
What should we do?

63
00:03:11,185 --> 00:03:13,241
- You can choose wherever you want.
- I don't mind.

64
00:03:13,266 --> 00:03:16,361
- Same here.
- Choose whatever bed you want.

65
00:03:16,386 --> 00:03:18,038
Okay. All right.

66
00:03:20,415 --> 00:03:21,415
This is nice.

67
00:03:22,155 --> 00:03:26,031
Did you check that out?
It's like a hot tub for us.

68
00:03:27,158 --> 00:03:28,636
(Glance)

69
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:33,014
It's a bit weird to go in a
hot tub with just the guys.

70
00:03:33,039 --> 00:03:36,279
- It's great for getting close.
- It's like a sauna.

71
00:03:36,346 --> 00:03:39,679
There will be four couples, so
the single guy can go in there alone.

72
00:03:40,335 --> 00:03:43,224
- That's a bit...
- You'll be steaming with anger.

73
00:03:43,505 --> 00:03:45,425
- That's too sad.
- It'll be too sad.

74
00:03:46,882 --> 00:03:48,080
Is this the dressing room?

75
00:03:48,105 --> 00:03:50,772
What? There's a separate
room for our clothes?

76
00:03:51,297 --> 00:03:52,630
Eh? What's this?

77
00:03:52,655 --> 00:03:53,767
