78
00:03:53,792 --> 00:03:54,792
No way!

79
00:03:55,889 --> 00:03:59,184
(Women's powder room)

80
00:03:59,593 --> 00:04:02,570
- Wow, this is nuts!
- I just got goosebumps.

81
00:04:03,386 --> 00:04:06,264
This is fascinating. I can't believe
there's a dressing table like this.

82
00:04:06,289 --> 00:04:07,352
This is clever.

83
00:04:08,651 --> 00:04:10,991
Wow, the bathroom interior is so pretty.

84
00:04:11,574 --> 00:04:14,415
- I'll take out my cosmetics first.
- Me, too.

85
00:04:15,291 --> 00:04:16,498
I want to do it in here.

86
00:04:17,545 --> 00:04:20,374
I'm the type who spreads out
all my cosmetics wherever I go.

87
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,399
Oh, really?

88
00:04:23,896 --> 00:04:27,761
(Ha-neul has a ton of hair devices.)

89
00:04:28,497 --> 00:04:31,258
Wow, this is cool. I didn't know
there was a dressing table like this.

90
00:04:33,225 --> 00:04:35,448
If you're sick, let me know.

91
00:04:35,591 --> 00:04:38,549
- You must have brought a lot of medicine.
- I'm like a pharmacy.

92
00:04:38,976 --> 00:04:41,675
I brought herbal tonic, too. Let
me know if you're not feeling well.

93
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:43,137
- Herbal tonic?
- Yes.

94
00:04:43,862 --> 00:04:45,449
(Peek)

95
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:48,865
Why are you writing down
that she brought medicine?

96
00:04:49,515 --> 00:04:51,001
- It's important.
- Bringing medicine?

97
00:04:51,026 --> 00:04:52,026
- Yes.
- I see.

98
00:04:53,559 --> 00:04:57,499
(Meanwhile, Ji-min
just stares at the others.)

99
00:04:57,797 --> 00:05:01,663
Ji-min is really quiet.

100
00:05:02,778 --> 00:05:04,326
(Sigh)

101
00:05:08,055 --> 00:05:09,055
I...

102
00:05:10,755 --> 00:05:13,929
feel like I don't belong here.

103
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,553
Why would you say that? Huh?

104
00:05:16,305 --> 00:05:18,952
Everyone was talking
about their experiences,

105
00:05:19,897 --> 00:05:21,297
but I don't have any.

106
00:05:24,461 --> 00:05:29,266
If I was at least 23 or 24, I
could've join in the conversation.

107
00:05:29,725 --> 00:05:32,212
- Oh no.
- But I shouldn't blame my age.

108
00:05:33,748 --> 00:05:35,700
I need to be more proactive.

109
00:05:38,603 --> 00:05:42,906
Everyone seemed to smoothly talk with
each other without any awkwardness.

110
00:05:45,222 --> 00:05:49,896
If I'm with just one other person
or in a small group, I can talk,

111
00:05:50,203 --> 00:05:54,393
but when we're all together,
it's hard to intervene.

112
00:05:57,361 --> 00:06:00,067
There are so many attractive women,

113
00:06:01,353 --> 00:06:03,349
and I'm like nothing compared to them.

114
00:06:04,129 --> 00:06:05,931
- Don't say that.
- Come on.

115
00:06:06,219 --> 00:06:09,485
- She's full of charms.
- She's really adorable.

116
00:06:09,683 --> 00:06:12,389
If Ji-min is a Love Catcher

117
00:06:12,414 --> 00:06:17,869
and one of the guys
try to take care of her...

118
00:06:17,992 --> 00:06:20,318
- She'll be attracted to him.
- She'll lean towards him.

119
00:06:20,988 --> 00:06:21,988
I'm curious.

120
00:06:23,115 --> 00:06:26,039
I'm sure each of you have someone
that you want to know more about.

121
00:06:26,064 --> 00:06:28,255
- There's one.
- One?

122
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,280
Who?

123
00:06:29,637 --> 00:06:31,107
- Yeo-min.
- I see.

124
00:06:31,132 --> 00:06:32,132
(Careful)

125
00:06:33,302 --> 00:06:35,556
That's why I was going to
go on a date with her today.

126
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:39,854
But I happened to run into him.

127
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:41,430
I'm sorry.

128
00:06:43,151 --> 00:06:44,363
Will you get in my car?

129
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:47,073
- I'm sorry.
- It's fine.

130
00:06:47,874 --> 00:06:51,446
This is really heavy.

131
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,165
So I went for a drive alone.

132
00:06:57,845 --> 00:07:01,004
It feels... It feels a bit iffy...

133
00:07:01,428 --> 00:07:05,563
You know, In-seong
showed up right in front of me.

134
00:07:07,085 --> 00:07:09,394
I'm sorry.

135
00:07:09,419 --> 00:07:13,064
She bowed 90 degrees.
I couldn't watch.

136
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:15,489
I hated how I was
standing in front of a cab.

137
00:07:16,127 --> 00:07:17,802
I felt really miserable then.

138
00:07:18,724 --> 00:07:20,858
It wasn't about the
rejection. I was miserable that

139
00:07:20,883 --> 00:07:22,852
I didn't buy a car. I kept
complaining about it.

140
00:07:22,877 --> 00:07:24,999
I felt like that even with a car.

141
00:07:26,781 --> 00:07:28,571
Mr. Porsche finally said something.

142
00:07:30,688 --> 00:07:32,284
Even with a Porsche.

143
00:07:32,657 --> 00:07:34,022
(Oops!)

144
00:07:34,392 --> 00:07:36,296
What's your ideal type?

145
00:07:37,157 --> 00:07:39,688
- I like women with pretty cheekbones.
- Cheekbones?

146
00:07:39,713 --> 00:07:41,563
- That's really unique.
- What if they pop out?

147
00:07:41,588 --> 00:07:43,542
- That's what I like.
- Really?

148
00:07:43,998 --> 00:07:46,093
I learned about face-reading.

149
00:07:47,938 --> 00:07:50,415
If you have nice cheekbones,
many people help you.

150
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,156
Oh, really?

151
00:07:52,481 --> 00:07:55,081
I don't go for girls
with cute personalities.

152
00:07:55,292 --> 00:07:58,207
I like down-to-earth ones
who are more like friends.

153
00:07:58,232 --> 00:08:01,258
As for appearances, I like
girls who look like cats.

154
00:08:02,874 --> 00:08:04,605
I think your ideal type is here then.

155
00:08:05,156 --> 00:08:11,298
That's why we talked on the way
here, and her personality wasn't bad.

156
00:08:12,043 --> 00:08:14,598
I can just tell she's down-to-earth.

157
00:08:15,299 --> 00:08:17,140
(Stare)

158
00:08:17,165 --> 00:08:18,315
They're subtle.

159
00:08:19,376 --> 00:08:21,955
I like women with pretty eyes.

160
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:25,618
Oh, Ji-min?

161
00:08:26,309 --> 00:08:27,801
They all have pretty eyes though.

162
00:08:28,679 --> 00:08:31,925
I like women with double
eyelids and big eyes.

163
00:08:33,143 --> 00:08:34,961
I think I'm attracted to
people with big eyes.

164
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,976
There's a subtle war of nerves.

165
00:08:41,001 --> 00:08:42,859
(Do these two men
have similar ideal types?)

166
00:08:43,878 --> 00:08:46,790
- It feels real now that
we're sitting like this. - I know.

167
00:08:47,572 --> 00:08:49,039
Who did you come with?

168
00:08:49,453 --> 00:08:51,780
- Jung-woo.
- Jung-woo.

169
00:08:51,805 --> 00:08:52,805
How was it?

170
00:08:53,141 --> 00:08:54,951
It was really comfortable.

171
00:08:54,976 --> 00:08:56,682
He was very friendly.

172
00:08:56,955 --> 00:08:58,637
So it was a comfortable ride.

173
00:08:58,662 --> 00:09:00,044
What about you, Yeo-min?

174
00:09:00,579 --> 00:09:04,618
There were two people I was
hoping would come pick me up.

175
00:09:04,973 --> 00:09:06,981
One came but not the other one.

176
00:09:07,649 --> 00:09:09,284
- One of them came?
- Yes.

177
00:09:09,309 --> 00:09:10,817
(Nod)

178
00:09:12,002 --> 00:09:14,135
What do I do?
What should I do?

179
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:16,524
So I probably came with him, right?

180
00:09:18,746 --> 00:09:20,809
So she was
interested in him, too.

181
00:09:20,834 --> 00:09:24,140
- That means she likes someone besides him.
- Right.

182
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:27,072
Unfortunately, that's not Jae-hyung.

183
00:09:27,336 --> 00:09:28,773
Oh no.

184
00:09:29,526 --> 00:09:31,217
That's some sad news.

185
00:09:31,242 --> 00:09:33,587
- Who picked you up?
- Me?

186
00:09:34,003 --> 00:09:36,320
- Yes.
- Su-won.

187
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:44,453
(This morning, Su-won
was waiting for Ha-neul.)

188
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:48,753
I was really worried that I'd
have to come here by myself.

189
00:09:48,987 --> 00:09:52,322
But he showed up, and I was grateful.

190
00:09:52,457 --> 00:09:54,957
- We must all feel the same way.
- Right.

191
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:59,216
Ji-min can't join their conversation.

192
00:10:00,340 --> 00:10:05,644
Could you tell the difference between
a Love Catcher and a Money Catcher?

193
00:10:06,117 --> 00:10:07,705
Honestly, I don't know.

194
00:10:07,730 --> 00:10:10,508
- Even if they're nice, I doubt them.
- Same here.

195
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:13,097
Even if they treat me
nicely, I get suspicious.

196
00:10:14,634 --> 00:10:16,768
- So we can't just be happy.
- Right.

197
00:10:16,935 --> 00:10:17,935
It's hard.

198
00:10:18,866 --> 00:10:19,866
How interesting.

199
00:10:21,314 --> 00:10:24,029
- It showed up as soon as
we talked about it. - That scared me.

200
00:10:24,054 --> 00:10:25,121
What's going on?

201
00:10:25,146 --> 00:10:27,738
What is it? What is it?

202
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,394
Oh, something popped up.

203
00:10:32,104 --> 00:10:33,238
What's happening?

204
00:10:35,565 --> 00:10:37,473
(That Man's Taste)

205
00:10:37,498 --> 00:10:38,854
"That Man's Taste"?

206
00:10:42,345 --> 00:10:44,377
- "That Man's Taste"?
- "That Man's Taste"?

207
00:10:44,402 --> 00:10:45,601
"That Man's Taste"?

208
00:10:45,626 --> 00:10:47,443
(Not sure)

209
00:10:47,468 --> 00:10:48,468
Is that all?

210
00:10:49,272 --> 00:10:52,552
(That Man's Date: Tonight, the
men will prepare a dinner date.)

211
00:10:52,744 --> 00:10:55,355
(The men will be in charge
of their first dinner together.)

212
00:10:55,469 --> 00:10:56,730
We're screwed.

213
00:10:58,108 --> 00:11:02,158
What? What's this?

214
00:11:05,177 --> 00:11:08,417
(The men will cook a dish for their date.)

215
00:11:08,442 --> 00:11:10,587
So the men are doing everything today.

216
00:11:11,432 --> 00:11:14,805
Since it's a "dinner date," does that
mean we won't all be eating together?

217
00:11:14,830 --> 00:11:17,205
Let's say each of the guys prepares a dish.

218
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:20,016
Maybe we have to choose which one we want?

219
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:23,894
- Oh! - So maybe we're going on
a date with whoever made that dish.

220
00:11:23,919 --> 00:11:25,175
But there are five guys.

221
00:11:25,532 --> 00:11:27,119
So one of them will eat alone?

222
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:29,320
(Cry)

223
00:11:29,519 --> 00:11:31,671
(That's cruel.)

224
00:11:32,279 --> 00:11:35,058
So are we making a dish
and giving it to the one we like?

225
00:11:35,083 --> 00:11:37,359
Or are they choosing the dish they like?

226
00:11:37,384 --> 00:11:41,426
Does that mean one of us will have
to eat the food we made by ourselves?

227
00:11:42,391 --> 00:11:43,391
Again?

228
00:11:43,931 --> 00:11:46,600
(Why are we already getting
a bad feeling about this...?)

229
00:11:47,492 --> 00:11:49,471
Jae-hyung, why did you
suddenly have a beard?

230
00:11:50,193 --> 00:11:54,974
- He had clear skin at first.
- Why did he get so haggard?

231
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:58,392
What can you make?
What will you cook?

232
00:11:59,498 --> 00:12:01,030
Well, steak and...

233
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:03,675
You're coming off strong.

234
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,405
Should I make pasta?

235
00:12:06,681 --> 00:12:08,053
I think he'll be a good cook.

236
00:12:08,284 --> 00:12:11,365
I made pasta before, and if that's
what he's gonna cook, I'm not making it.

237
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,217
I think we'll get compared then.

238
00:12:13,242 --> 00:12:14,575
I'm not good either.

239
00:12:15,229 --> 00:12:19,230
It's not over yet, and I want
to do it as if I'm starting over.

240
00:12:21,029 --> 00:12:22,909
- Should we go get ready?
- Sure.

241
00:12:23,103 --> 00:12:24,103
Let's go.

242
00:12:25,693 --> 00:12:29,750
I think we got close at
the speed of light.

243
00:12:30,189 --> 00:12:31,919
It's a war. Isn't this a battlefield?

244
00:12:34,575 --> 00:12:37,900
- They only have a week.
- I'm excited.

245
00:12:38,532 --> 00:12:39,666
Wow, what's this?

246
00:12:40,874 --> 00:12:42,405
I guess we're making it here.

247
00:12:42,430 --> 00:12:44,708
Gosh, why don't I have confidence?

248
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:47,530
- What's in there?
- Let's open it.

249
00:12:47,555 --> 00:12:50,024
(They start scanning
the refrigerator first.)

250
00:12:50,059 --> 00:12:51,297
I have no idea.

251
00:12:51,590 --> 00:12:53,528
What do you know how to make?
What will you cook?

252
00:12:53,553 --> 00:12:55,665
- I'm going to make seaweed soup.
- Seaweed soup?

253
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:57,875
I love seaweed soup.
Should we have dinner together?

254
00:12:58,322 --> 00:13:01,991
Is there some Parmesan here?

255
00:13:02,016 --> 00:13:03,016
Here's steak.

256
00:13:04,011 --> 00:13:07,120
(One by one, the ingredients come
together. Who will eat their food?)

257
00:13:07,488 --> 00:13:10,458
I wonder what the girls are doing.
Are they just talking in their room?

258
00:13:11,129 --> 00:13:12,922
I wonder what kind
of dishes will be there.

259
00:13:13,155 --> 00:13:14,917
I'm curious. What will they make?

260
00:13:15,284 --> 00:13:17,991
Is his name Jae-hyung? I think
he's a good cook. - Right.

261
00:13:18,598 --> 00:13:20,987
He said he likes cooking,
so he's definitely good at it.

262
00:13:21,514 --> 00:13:23,529
I love rice. I need it.

263
00:13:24,587 --> 00:13:25,611
I can't eat without rice.

264
00:13:26,665 --> 00:13:28,733
(Won-jae's dinner
date menu: katsudon)

265
00:13:29,148 --> 00:13:30,489
Something smells good.

266
00:13:31,426 --> 00:13:34,603
(Jae-hyung's dinner date
menu: wrapped bacon)

267
00:13:34,628 --> 00:13:36,590
- It's really hard.
- What are you making?

268
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:38,210
Me? Shrimp katsu sandwich.

269
00:13:39,689 --> 00:13:41,961
I don't know. I don't
think it'll turn out nice.

270
00:13:41,986 --> 00:13:45,154
- It looks awesome.
- It needs to taste good.

271
00:13:45,776 --> 00:13:47,493
I think it'll definitely
taste good, too.

272
00:13:47,684 --> 00:13:50,564
(Everyone seems to be cooking smoothly.)

273
00:13:51,598 --> 00:13:55,211
(He tries it over and over and over again.

274
00:13:55,236 --> 00:13:57,422
He's not eating dinner, is he?

275
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:02,512
(It's not easy to season the seaweed
soup with the right amount of salt.)

276
00:14:02,707 --> 00:14:04,080
You can feel the sincerity, right?

277
00:14:04,105 --> 00:14:05,789
Yes, because I saw you make it.

278
00:14:05,814 --> 00:14:08,918
Right. I think I'd be more drawn
to seaweed soup than steak.

279
00:14:08,943 --> 00:14:09,943
Same here.

280
00:14:10,704 --> 00:14:12,960
(The fall night deepens.)

281
00:14:13,782 --> 00:14:17,250
(A war-like romance unfolding in Love
Mansion located in the middle of the city)

282
00:14:18,573 --> 00:14:20,756
- They're eating outside.
- It's outdoors.

283
00:14:22,799 --> 00:14:25,585
(Ji-min's wonderful Mille-feuille
Nabe with warm soup)

284
00:14:26,581 --> 00:14:27,705
Wow, is that tiramisu?

285
00:14:27,730 --> 00:14:30,327
(Won-jae even prepared
dessert. Katsudong and tiramisu.)

286
00:14:31,099 --> 00:14:32,643
(Su-won's shrimp katsu sandwich and

287
00:14:32,668 --> 00:14:34,461
spaghetti aglio e olio
with charming plating)

288
00:14:34,486 --> 00:14:36,812
(Jung-woo's home cooked meal with sincerity)

289
00:14:37,406 --> 00:14:40,311
(Jae-hyung's abundant
western meal of various dishes)

290
00:14:40,336 --> 00:14:42,731
- It's like VIPS.
- VIPS!

291
00:14:44,236 --> 00:14:46,927
It's a bit chilly, so I think
everyone would want to eat that.

292
00:14:47,541 --> 00:14:48,541
It's warm.

293
00:14:50,863 --> 00:14:53,506
But they're just coming out,
so they might not be cold.

294
00:14:54,755 --> 00:14:56,105
They all seem worried.

295
00:14:56,977 --> 00:14:57,977
And Won-jae...

296
00:14:58,863 --> 00:15:00,782
They might not choose based on the food.

297
00:15:01,457 --> 00:15:03,634
(Who is Won-jae waiting for?)

298
00:15:03,659 --> 00:15:10,044
I thought it'd be nice if I could serve
dinner to Yeo-min, who came with me today.

299
00:15:12,002 --> 00:15:13,979
(Nervous)

300
00:15:15,468 --> 00:15:19,182
I think Ha-neul will choose me.
If she doesn't, that'd be a twist.

301
00:15:19,844 --> 00:15:21,645
- He's only thinking about her.
- Right.

302
00:15:23,553 --> 00:15:26,642
(Soon, it's time for dinner.)

303
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:27,749
Where are they?

304
00:15:28,442 --> 00:15:30,576
- I don't smell anything.
- Where's the food?

305
00:15:31,738 --> 00:15:32,738
My goodness.

306
00:15:33,551 --> 00:15:36,751
- It's pretty at night.
- It looks even better.

307
00:15:39,094 --> 00:15:42,555
(They head there with excited steps.)

308
00:15:43,562 --> 00:15:46,442
- They're all sitting separately?
- Oh my gosh.

309
00:15:47,157 --> 00:15:49,683
(They're getting closer and closer.)

310
00:15:49,708 --> 00:15:51,806
- This is crazy.
- What's all this?

311
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,927
- Gosh!
- I'm nervous!

312
00:15:54,952 --> 00:15:56,935
(Shutting his eyes)

313
00:15:57,719 --> 00:16:01,870
- My goodness.
- What do we do? How can we choose?

314
00:16:02,327 --> 00:16:03,604
They must be so nervous.

315
00:16:04,692 --> 00:16:05,924
I'm going insane.

316
00:16:05,949 --> 00:16:07,322
- Did you choose?
- Hmm?

317
00:16:07,465 --> 00:16:09,800
Do you have someone in mind
or do you need to look first?

318
00:16:11,107 --> 00:16:12,495
Dinner date.

319
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:15,932
I'm comfortable around
Won-jae, so I was thinking of

320
00:16:15,957 --> 00:16:18,864
eating with him. And I thought
I owe him that much, too.

321
00:16:19,837 --> 00:16:24,243
But I also wanted to try
talking to someone else.

322
00:16:24,494 --> 00:16:29,279
Honestly, it's our first meeting, so it's
a good idea to get to know everyone.

323
00:16:30,039 --> 00:16:34,301
I wanted to choose Ji-min, whom
I talked with the most last night.

324
00:16:34,389 --> 00:16:35,389
I knew it.

325
00:16:35,846 --> 00:16:40,854
I was thinking of either Su-won or Ji-min.

326
00:16:41,892 --> 00:16:44,678
- Oh, it's not just Su-won she has in mind.
- Right.

327
00:16:44,703 --> 00:16:47,694
I think everyone's thinking carefully.

328
00:16:50,266 --> 00:16:52,861
They really made a lot of preparations.

329
00:16:54,031 --> 00:16:58,637
(The women are carefully
checking out the dishes.)

330
00:17:00,184 --> 00:17:03,181
(Why are they so shocked?)

331
00:17:03,914 --> 00:17:04,914
Oh, wow.

332
00:17:06,408 --> 00:17:08,234
I suddenly imagined something sad.

333
00:17:08,571 --> 00:17:10,459
I don't think he'll eat alone.

334
00:17:10,484 --> 00:17:12,478
- Same here.
- I have a good feeling.

335
00:17:13,295 --> 00:17:14,295
Oh, wow.

336
00:17:15,222 --> 00:17:18,706
It was my first time putting
so much heart in cooking.

337
00:17:18,731 --> 00:17:20,732
I thought at least one
person will come.

338
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:23,348
It's Korean food.

339
00:17:23,373 --> 00:17:25,126
(Perk)

340
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,652
He made a lot.

341
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:30,821
(In-seong is lingering
near Jung-woo's table.)

342
00:17:32,841 --> 00:17:34,509
(In-seong turns away.)

343
00:17:34,938 --> 00:17:36,469
(Too bad.)

344
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:38,736
They're walking in a group.

345
00:17:39,222 --> 00:17:41,254
Ladies, this isn't a food court!

346
00:17:42,304 --> 00:17:43,994
The guys are waiting so desperately.

347
00:17:46,904 --> 00:17:48,477
I choose...

348
00:17:48,842 --> 00:17:50,366
I prepared warm food.

349
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:55,960
- I think I made up my mind.
- Me, too.

350
00:17:56,407 --> 00:17:58,296
Who is it? Where will they go?

351
00:17:59,277 --> 00:18:01,507
What will happen?
What about the guy no one chooses?

352
00:18:04,289 --> 00:18:07,725
I made my decision.
I'm going to eat warm food.

353
00:18:09,087 --> 00:18:10,381
I want to sit here, too...

354
00:18:13,052 --> 00:18:16,099
He didn't get picked before,
but the tables turned quickly.

355
00:18:16,782 --> 00:18:17,827
(Fixed gaze)

356
00:18:17,860 --> 00:18:19,954
- Ha-neul!
- She seems to be going towards him.

357
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:24,720
- You're going to sit here, too?
- Yeah.

358
00:18:27,509 --> 00:18:28,575
What's going on?

359
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,377
He suddenly became Mr. Popular.

360
00:18:30,402 --> 00:18:33,165
- Didn't he get almost all the votes?
- Yeah.

361
00:18:33,190 --> 00:18:34,654
So Mille-Feuille Nabe, huh?

362
00:18:35,035 --> 00:18:36,338
(Why would you write that down?)

363
00:18:36,363 --> 00:18:37,473
I'm sorry, but...

364
00:18:38,865 --> 00:18:39,928
That's hilarious!

365
00:18:39,953 --> 00:18:42,388
You're jotting down the oddest things.

366
00:18:43,251 --> 00:18:44,854
- You're going to sit here, too?
- Yeah.

367
00:18:46,094 --> 00:18:47,094
(Glance)

368
00:18:49,011 --> 00:18:50,773
He must have gotten shocked.

369
00:18:50,798 --> 00:18:53,067
- No way.
- What do we do?

370
00:18:55,750 --> 00:18:59,772
(He can't hide his joy about
suddenly receiving most of the votes.)

371
00:19:02,168 --> 00:19:03,620
What's going on?

372
00:19:03,811 --> 00:19:06,344
- He picked the right menu.
- Oh my god.

373
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:08,196
Wow.

374
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:11,116
Wait a minute.

375
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,562
Oh no.

376
00:19:16,587 --> 00:19:20,319
(They try to smile, but they
feel a wave of disappointment.)

377
00:19:21,584 --> 00:19:23,175
It's delicious. It's good.

378
00:19:23,977 --> 00:19:25,246
The dishes... Hang on.

379
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:29,124
Hello.

380
00:19:29,149 --> 00:19:31,601
(In-seong has chosen Jung-woo.)

381
00:19:32,467 --> 00:19:35,397
Just as expected!
In-seong went to Jung-woo.

382
00:19:36,658 --> 00:19:39,394
(The women have made their choices.)

383
00:19:39,819 --> 00:19:47,672
(Su-won, Won-jae, and
Jae-hyung are all alone.)

384
00:19:48,374 --> 00:19:49,771
Gosh, this is hilarious.

385
00:19:50,853 --> 00:19:53,330
- Enjoy!
- Dig in.

386
00:19:53,657 --> 00:19:54,657
Enjoy.

387
00:19:54,682 --> 00:19:57,255
(The three of them will
enjoy their solo dinner dates.)

388
00:19:57,413 --> 00:19:59,051
He's shocked.

389
00:19:59,872 --> 00:20:01,824
I had no idea you three would choose me.

390
00:20:02,215 --> 00:20:04,651
- We didn't either.
- We had no idea. Seriously.

391
00:20:05,019 --> 00:20:06,543
I'll give each of you one.

392
00:20:08,062 --> 00:20:10,936
I hope Ji-min will be able to talk well.

393
00:20:11,726 --> 00:20:12,924
This is amazing.

394
00:20:14,291 --> 00:20:16,608
- Thank you.
- Would you like some soup?

395
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:18,095
Soup? A little, please.

396
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:20,407
(Totally sweet)

397
00:20:21,877 --> 00:20:24,298
- Just enough to cover the ingredients.
- Okay. This much.

398
00:20:24,976 --> 00:20:25,976
Thanks.

399
00:20:27,091 --> 00:20:29,582
- Wait, Ha-neul. Have some more meat.
- Okay.

400
00:20:29,607 --> 00:20:31,180
Let me give you some.

401
00:20:32,492 --> 00:20:35,127
- He's only giving her meat.
- Why is he giving her more meat?

402
00:20:35,278 --> 00:20:36,559
(Smile)

403
00:20:37,164 --> 00:20:38,800
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

404
00:20:38,825 --> 00:20:40,317
How did you even make this?

405
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:42,953
- How is it? Good?
- Mmm, it's really delicious.

406
00:20:42,978 --> 00:20:44,654
- I'm glad.
- It's really yummy!

407
00:20:46,946 --> 00:20:50,264
- Ji-min's eyes look really sad.
- I know.

408
00:20:50,289 --> 00:20:51,289
Right?

409
00:20:52,275 --> 00:20:54,704
I'll give you some more.
Eat it all. I made a lot.

410
00:20:54,977 --> 00:20:57,858
I'll be full even if I
don't eat. Seriously.

411
00:20:59,784 --> 00:21:01,569
Ji-min is all about Ha-neul.

412
00:21:02,105 --> 00:21:05,668
For the first time, I realized what it
means to feel full even if you don't eat.

413
00:21:06,105 --> 00:21:07,799
(Deep sigh)

414
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:11,737
He's sighing too loudly.

415
00:21:11,762 --> 00:21:14,429
(Ha-neul is conscious of Su-won's sigh.)

416
00:21:14,846 --> 00:21:17,870
(His expression is
growing stiffer and stiffer.)

417
00:21:18,747 --> 00:21:20,033
Would you like some more?

418
00:21:20,805 --> 00:21:23,711
- He's only taking care of her!
- He's making it too obvious!

419
00:21:24,610 --> 00:21:27,610
- I can't look in your direction.
- Why not? Why not?

420
00:21:29,561 --> 00:21:32,164
- I just can't.
- Why not?

421
00:21:32,879 --> 00:21:34,206
Don't look at him.

422
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,863
You can look. Go ahead.

423
00:21:39,847 --> 00:21:41,291
I'm enjoying my food alone.

424
00:21:43,156 --> 00:21:46,688
To sum it up, I felt pathetic
since I didn't get picked.

425
00:21:47,486 --> 00:21:49,985
- Please tell me if my double
eyelids appear. - Let me see.

426
00:21:50,504 --> 00:21:51,504
They're here.

427
00:21:53,726 --> 00:21:58,094
(Su-won was conscious of those two.)

428
00:21:59,689 --> 00:22:05,509
I couldn't hide my emotions, so I tried
to look far away and control my feelings.

429
00:22:06,117 --> 00:22:08,410
- Goodness.
- This is so sad!

430
00:22:09,732 --> 00:22:16,390
While eating, I experienced
emotions I've never felt before.

431
00:22:20,434 --> 00:22:23,632
- It seems like Ha-neul is very
conscious of him, right? - Yes.

432
00:22:24,319 --> 00:22:26,723
If I lean towards one person
starting from the first day,

433
00:22:27,202 --> 00:22:30,258
then I don't think I'll have
time to get to know the others.

434
00:22:30,580 --> 00:22:34,849
I wanted to choose someone
else, and for me, that was Ji-min.

435
00:22:35,131 --> 00:22:38,662
I wanted to talk with him.
I wanted to get to know him more.

436
00:22:40,486 --> 00:22:43,017
- Oh no. You need to eat, too.
- No, I'm totally fine.

437
00:22:43,042 --> 00:22:45,647
I'm really full just
watching you girls eat.

438
00:22:45,995 --> 00:22:47,689
(Guilty. Worried.)

439
00:22:47,782 --> 00:22:49,446
But how about you
at least have a bite?

440
00:22:49,939 --> 00:22:52,130
As soon as you three sat down, I got full.

441
00:22:52,670 --> 00:22:54,067
(Truly happy)

442
00:22:55,542 --> 00:22:57,962
- How did you think about making this?
- I know.

443
00:22:58,330 --> 00:23:03,458
During Lunar New Year, my older
sister offered to teach me to cook.

444
00:23:05,027 --> 00:23:06,844
- Can I eat this?
- Is it good?

445
00:23:06,869 --> 00:23:09,974
I had no idea what I made
that day would come in handy.

446
00:23:10,387 --> 00:23:12,413
- You only made it once?
- Twice.

447
00:23:12,438 --> 00:23:13,438
Twice.

448
00:23:13,592 --> 00:23:15,759
What happened to the
spaghetti aglio e olio?

449
00:23:16,277 --> 00:23:19,459
- Are you good at cooking?
- Are you?

450
00:23:19,484 --> 00:23:24,330
I felt bad that others would have to cook
for me, so I practiced a couple dishes.

451
00:23:24,841 --> 00:23:26,775
- You practiced?
- For real?

452
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:29,026
I tried making spaghetti aglio e olio.

453
00:23:30,419 --> 00:23:33,594
It wasn't bad, so I'll
cook it for you one day.

454
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:36,972
Although I don't know if you'll eat it.

455
00:23:36,997 --> 00:23:39,831
Oh, so that's what Ji-min meant?

456
00:23:40,006 --> 00:23:42,159
Oh, they were at different
tables, but she heard it?

457
00:23:42,184 --> 00:23:44,399
- She was listening to him.
- She was listening to him.

458
00:23:44,424 --> 00:23:49,206
- Really?
- She liked him from the beginning.

459
00:23:49,661 --> 00:23:51,598
What happened to the
spaghetti aglio e olio?

460
00:23:51,623 --> 00:23:54,490
I was going to make it, but a
lot of people were making pasta.

461
00:23:55,095 --> 00:23:59,844
- Oh. - I'll try it next time,
even if it's not an event like this.

462
00:24:01,674 --> 00:24:03,031
I'll make it for you.

463
00:24:08,223 --> 00:24:10,761
(While preparing the final
course, he got eggs on his hands.)

464
00:24:11,287 --> 00:24:12,539
(Thinking)

465
00:24:13,417 --> 00:24:16,496
- I think you'll need this.
- Thank you.

466
00:24:17,618 --> 00:24:19,912
Okay! Nice!

467
00:24:20,258 --> 00:24:23,202
- I'm starting to root for her.
- Me, too!

468
00:24:23,778 --> 00:24:25,151
I'm honestly full.

469
00:24:25,176 --> 00:24:26,833
(Chew, chew)

470
00:24:26,858 --> 00:24:27,858
She's adorable.

471
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:29,630
(His gaze goes towards her more and more.)

472
00:24:29,655 --> 00:24:31,473
I want to eat this
for breakfast, too.

473
00:24:31,498 --> 00:24:34,539
- Oh my gosh.
- Yang Ji-min is...

474
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:36,978
a Love Catcher.

475
00:24:38,173 --> 00:24:39,180
She really is!

476
00:24:39,205 --> 00:24:40,561
(You decided that already?!)

477
00:24:40,586 --> 00:24:43,056
- She really is.
- This is the real deal.

478
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:45,371
Thank you.

479
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:47,951
I'll try it first.

480
00:24:48,534 --> 00:24:50,439
- They're just on a normal date.
- Yeah.

481
00:24:52,799 --> 00:24:55,515
(He put a lot of effort in it, and
he's anticipating her reaction.)

482
00:24:55,626 --> 00:24:57,025
It's very good.

483
00:24:58,012 --> 00:25:00,076
- You mean it?
- Yes. Really. I can't lie.

484
00:25:00,913 --> 00:25:04,103
I never guessed I would
have homemade food here.

485
00:25:04,931 --> 00:25:06,630
Are you taking any tests soon?

486
00:25:07,865 --> 00:25:09,235
(In-seong cracks up at his joke.)

487
00:25:09,260 --> 00:25:10,635
The soup is cold, isn't it?

488
00:25:10,906 --> 00:25:12,144
It's good even if it's cold.

489
00:25:12,169 --> 00:25:13,987
It's really delicious.
I'm not just saying it.

490
00:25:14,012 --> 00:25:15,527
- Really?
- Yes, it's scrumptious.

491
00:25:15,966 --> 00:25:17,435
So lovey-dovey.

492
00:25:18,121 --> 00:25:20,200
You're...

493
00:25:21,541 --> 00:25:24,829
- older than me.
- A lot older.

494
00:25:25,534 --> 00:25:31,233
It's a bit awkward to regard you formally.

495
00:25:32,056 --> 00:25:36,631
- Then what would you like to do?
- Can I casually call you by your name?

496
00:25:36,656 --> 00:25:37,656
Sure.

497
00:25:38,396 --> 00:25:39,983
Can I casually call
you by your name?

498
00:25:40,008 --> 00:25:41,715
(Tickle, tickle)

499
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:43,342
(I'm getting all excited!)

500
00:25:43,367 --> 00:25:45,830
First off, those two are
definitely Love Catchers.

501
00:25:48,654 --> 00:25:52,559
- Can I casually call you by your name?
- Sure.

502
00:25:54,596 --> 00:25:58,073
- You can regard me casually, too.
- Okay.

503
00:25:58,665 --> 00:26:00,728
- Gosh!
- They look great together.

504
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:02,642
(Shy)

505
00:26:06,477 --> 00:26:10,021
(In-seong shows big
reactions every time she eats.)

506
00:26:11,678 --> 00:26:13,503
This is amazing.

507
00:26:15,759 --> 00:26:17,450
Seriously. It's perfect.

508
00:26:17,839 --> 00:26:19,389
She has great reactions.

509
00:26:19,551 --> 00:26:21,351
I need to work harder then.

510
00:26:23,494 --> 00:26:24,999
(Now, she hums.)

511
00:26:25,169 --> 00:26:27,295
I think you have a knack
for making people happy.

512
00:26:27,670 --> 00:26:28,670
Oh my.

513
00:26:30,808 --> 00:26:32,578
I was embarrassed
while making this earlier.

514
00:26:32,603 --> 00:26:35,628
- Why?
- I had to taste it 20 times.

515
00:26:35,735 --> 00:26:37,989
- You were embarrassed about that?
- Yeah.

516
00:26:38,135 --> 00:26:41,658
You might have tasted it 20
times, but it turned out fantastic.

517
00:26:42,123 --> 00:26:43,908
The one who's eating it is fantastic.

518
00:26:45,587 --> 00:26:47,444
It felt like my birthday.

519
00:26:47,469 --> 00:26:48,602
- Really?
- Yup.

520
00:26:50,198 --> 00:26:53,057
- Oh my goodness!
- They're really lovey-dovey.

521
00:26:53,970 --> 00:26:56,158
(Happy/Sad)

522
00:26:56,183 --> 00:27:02,893
I was angry about all the time
and effort I put into these dishes.

523
00:27:03,344 --> 00:27:07,860
But I was really humiliated in the morning,

524
00:27:08,118 --> 00:27:11,102
so I got used to it and I
just found the situation funny.

525
00:27:13,828 --> 00:27:15,192
This is hilarious.

526
00:27:16,204 --> 00:27:19,531
- No, Jae-hyung!
- He can't lose his self-esteem.

527
00:27:19,556 --> 00:27:20,740
He can't!

528
00:27:22,158 --> 00:27:25,387
I thought at least one
person would come to me.

529
00:27:28,210 --> 00:27:30,726
But no one came.
No one came.

530
00:27:33,025 --> 00:27:36,128
(This dinner wasn't easy
even for the strong steel troop.)

531
00:27:36,362 --> 00:27:37,857
(We're upset, too.)

532
00:27:37,882 --> 00:27:42,730
The most surprising thing was that
Ji-min, who didn't get selected as

533
00:27:42,870 --> 00:27:47,006
an escort during the first date
and had to come alone in a cab,

534
00:27:47,256 --> 00:27:50,430
got chosen by three
women for the dinner date.

535
00:27:51,044 --> 00:27:55,795
It kind of felt like Ji-min was
second place in the girls' hearts.

536
00:27:55,820 --> 00:28:01,098
But now, after the first date, they
wanted to get to know him better.

537
00:28:01,231 --> 00:28:04,022
Aren't you curious if
this fact that he received

538
00:28:04,047 --> 00:28:06,609
a majority of votes will
benefit or harm him?

539
00:28:07,459 --> 00:28:12,141
Women might think, "Oh,
do I have a lot of rivals?"

540
00:28:13,044 --> 00:28:15,131
And the men might be wary of him.

541
00:28:15,156 --> 00:28:17,380
- Wow, that's true.
- It could happen.

542
00:28:17,405 --> 00:28:23,186
What's intriguing was that we could clearly
see that Ji-min was interested in Ha-neul.

543
00:28:23,211 --> 00:28:24,508
- Right.
- Yes.

544
00:28:24,955 --> 00:28:29,632
And Ji-min tried to make her
feelings about him more apparent.

545
00:28:29,657 --> 00:28:31,354
- She mustered up the courage.
- Right.

546
00:28:31,379 --> 00:28:33,675
- She tried to express herself more.
- Exactly.

547
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:36,828
And if Ahn Ji-min is
actually a Money Catcher...

548
00:28:40,144 --> 00:28:41,428
then he needs to go for her.

549
00:28:41,453 --> 00:28:45,248
Oh, because it's obvious
that she has feelings for him?

550
00:28:45,578 --> 00:28:50,896
I just want In-seong and Jung-woo
to walk down the aisle already.

551
00:28:50,921 --> 00:28:53,179
- But they might not end up
together, right? - Right.

552
00:28:55,248 --> 00:28:58,271
(Su-won, Jae-hyung, and
Won-jae wrap up their dates first.)

553
00:28:58,296 --> 00:29:00,028
Why did we leave the door open?

554
00:29:00,714 --> 00:29:07,071
I think the women want to
get to know different men.

555
00:29:07,245 --> 00:29:08,809
I'm not sure. Maybe.

556
00:29:09,136 --> 00:29:11,327
But I think they just made up their minds.

557
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:14,710
I've never cooked so hard in my life.

558
00:29:14,735 --> 00:29:15,735
Seriously.

559
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:17,037
(Same here.)

560
00:29:17,062 --> 00:29:19,662
You really worked hard without talking.

561
00:29:21,028 --> 00:29:23,472
I'm sure he's thirsty.

562
00:29:23,642 --> 00:29:25,318
God, this is making me crazy.

563
00:29:25,343 --> 00:29:27,176
But I'm fine. I'm all good now.

564
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,378
But when I was eating,

565
00:29:30,227 --> 00:29:32,777
I had no idea what to do
about my facial expression.

566
00:29:33,645 --> 00:29:35,178
But now, it's whatever.

567
00:29:35,577 --> 00:29:38,354
I looked into the far distance.

568
00:29:39,922 --> 00:29:42,200
I just ate the food 'cause I was hungry.

569
00:29:42,757 --> 00:29:44,376
- I ate, too.
- Same here.

570
00:29:45,585 --> 00:29:47,260
The food I made was delicious.

571
00:29:49,035 --> 00:29:51,543
But it was almost like a set-up.

572
00:29:51,988 --> 00:29:53,870
They went "I made up
mind" and just sat there.

573
00:29:53,895 --> 00:29:55,969
Or they could all be Money
Catchers who are aiming

574
00:29:56,369 --> 00:29:58,603
for him because they
think he's a Love Catcher.

575
00:29:58,786 --> 00:30:00,186
Yeah, you're right.

576
00:30:00,211 --> 00:30:02,267
I see Jae-hyung has a strong mentality.

577
00:30:02,770 --> 00:30:04,969
- He's healthy.
- Yeah.

578
00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:08,018
They could've thought
he was a Love Catcher,

579
00:30:08,043 --> 00:30:10,078
or they could've wanted
to know him better.

580
00:30:10,399 --> 00:30:12,533
Or maybe his food looked good.

581
00:30:12,558 --> 00:30:14,836
I think that'd be the best explanation.

582
00:30:14,861 --> 00:30:17,474
There's no time to get to know them.

583
00:30:18,208 --> 00:30:20,185
I didn't even get to talk to them.

584
00:30:21,442 --> 00:30:22,647
What should I do?

585
00:30:22,672 --> 00:30:24,848
(It seems to slowly dawn
on him that he's in a crisis.)

586
00:30:24,873 --> 00:30:26,668
You're back.

587
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:30,233
Did you have a fun date?

588
00:30:31,214 --> 00:30:32,365
I won't say anything.

589
00:30:32,390 --> 00:30:34,747
It's fine. It could happen.

590
00:30:34,772 --> 00:30:38,552
But there's something you need to know.

591
00:30:38,699 --> 00:30:42,324
I realized that, rather
than being interested in me,

592
00:30:42,349 --> 00:30:45,904
they were more drawn
towards the warmth of the food.

593
00:30:46,759 --> 00:30:49,933
- So it's about warm food.
- Right.

594
00:30:50,254 --> 00:30:52,833
They only chose the warm foods.

595
00:30:53,289 --> 00:30:54,966
They chose me because the food was warm.

596
00:30:55,164 --> 00:30:56,164
It wasn't...

597
00:30:58,676 --> 00:31:00,406
Su-won doesn't look happy at all.

598
00:31:00,431 --> 00:31:02,773
Because Ji-min went on a date with Ha-neul.

599
00:31:02,798 --> 00:31:04,878
He does look very uncomfortable.

600
00:31:07,328 --> 00:31:10,122
I never want to think about
these past two days again.

601
00:31:10,147 --> 00:31:11,495
(Jae-hyung's cute.)

602
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:13,117
I worked really hard on those dishes.

603
00:31:13,255 --> 00:31:14,730
- I know.
- It's only been one day.

604
00:31:17,211 --> 00:31:20,488
(There's a lot on his mind.)

605
00:31:21,391 --> 00:31:24,176
It's called observing.

606
00:31:24,982 --> 00:31:30,275
When I get to know someone,
I tend to keep an eye on them.

607
00:31:33,489 --> 00:31:35,569
I should start talking to them tomorrow.

608
00:31:36,385 --> 00:31:39,754
(The men are having a good time
because of Jae-hyung's honest charms.)

609
00:31:39,779 --> 00:31:43,013
- Be nice to them, okay?
- Who are you going to talk to?

610
00:31:43,572 --> 00:31:45,851
Not you guys.

611
00:31:45,876 --> 00:31:48,890
(Who will Jae-hyung talk with?)

612
00:31:49,188 --> 00:31:52,109
I can't look at the guys' faces.

613
00:31:52,447 --> 00:31:54,003
Wow, but seriously...

614
00:31:54,653 --> 00:31:57,019
They cooked for about
two and a half hours.

615
00:31:57,627 --> 00:32:00,634
- It'd be fine if we were
just eating food... - I felt bad.

616
00:32:00,659 --> 00:32:03,084
They put a lot of heart into it.

617
00:32:03,348 --> 00:32:08,006
- They made the food thinking
someone was going to eat it. - Of course.

618
00:32:08,031 --> 00:32:09,398
(Concerned)

619
00:32:09,423 --> 00:32:10,892
If it were me, I would've cried.

620
00:32:10,917 --> 00:32:13,292
I think I would've run away.

621
00:32:13,768 --> 00:32:14,951
Or jump in the pool.

622
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:21,075
I was really sorry, and I
felt a bit uncomfortable.

623
00:32:21,516 --> 00:32:25,105
Su-won was eating alone
behind me, and he kept sighing.

624
00:32:25,773 --> 00:32:27,230
(Sigh)

625
00:32:27,255 --> 00:32:29,270
(Peek)

626
00:32:29,599 --> 00:32:31,535
I was sitting on pins and needles.

627
00:32:31,831 --> 00:32:32,934
Oh dear.

628
00:32:32,959 --> 00:32:36,235
I think the love lines are slowly changing.

629
00:32:37,073 --> 00:32:40,654
In a bit, we will reveal how many
Love Coins they get for the first time.

630
00:32:41,571 --> 00:32:46,546
During the lodging period, they
can take a Love Coin and insert

631
00:32:46,571 --> 00:32:51,313
it in the locker of the one they
like anytime during the day.

632
00:32:51,338 --> 00:32:52,338
Oh my!

633
00:32:53,157 --> 00:32:55,604
(The women's lodging)

634
00:32:55,903 --> 00:32:56,903
(Startled)

635
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:01,326
Oh my god! That scared me!

636
00:33:02,297 --> 00:33:04,479
- What's that?
- Something appeared on the screen.

637
00:33:04,504 --> 00:33:06,221
There's something on the screen!

638
00:33:06,326 --> 00:33:09,318
- Are they telling us to check our lockers?
- Oh, probably.

639
00:33:12,244 --> 00:33:16,206
(Please check to see
who is interested in you.)

640
00:33:16,231 --> 00:33:18,725
I knew it!

641
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:23,086
(Their first time checking the locker
is filled with worries and excitement.)

642
00:33:23,766 --> 00:33:24,766
We can check it today.

643
00:33:25,562 --> 00:33:27,305
We might feel pathetic again.

644
00:33:28,985 --> 00:33:31,731
- I feel uneasy.
- I'm super nervous.

645
00:33:34,475 --> 00:33:36,895
Ji-min can't hide his joy.

646
00:33:38,311 --> 00:33:39,777
This is unpredictable.

647
00:33:40,728 --> 00:33:43,149
Gosh, I really can't see it!

648
00:33:43,778 --> 00:33:46,374
- I'll be back.
- Bye.

649
00:33:46,750 --> 00:33:48,329
In-seong is going first.

650
00:33:54,259 --> 00:33:56,893
I think she'll anticipate one coin.

651
00:33:57,555 --> 00:34:00,087
(Room of Expressing Love Interests)

652
00:34:00,112 --> 00:34:03,217
Jung-woo and I were together the whole day,

653
00:34:03,579 --> 00:34:04,579
so I think...

654
00:34:05,962 --> 00:34:08,938
I think finding our
differences would be faster.

655
00:34:09,385 --> 00:34:12,656
- Can I casually call you by your name?
- Sure.

656
00:34:13,055 --> 00:34:16,017
- What if she doesn't get any coins?
- She should at least have one.

657
00:34:16,747 --> 00:34:21,269
(Lee In-seong/
Did she guess correctly?)

658
00:34:21,931 --> 00:34:24,645
- There has to be a coin.
- There's a coin for sure, right?

659
00:34:27,507 --> 00:34:29,746
- I knew it!
- What a relief.

660
00:34:29,771 --> 00:34:32,446
(Lee In-seong: 1 Vote)

661
00:34:37,737 --> 00:34:39,613
- You're back!
- You're back?

662
00:34:42,293 --> 00:34:43,880
She can't hide her expression.

663
00:34:43,905 --> 00:34:47,112
- She's smiling too widely.
- She can't make a poker face.

664
00:34:47,529 --> 00:34:48,861
(Beam)

665
00:34:48,886 --> 00:34:50,243
What's going on?

666
00:34:51,258 --> 00:34:52,618
Is it a good thing or not?

667
00:34:53,719 --> 00:34:55,377
I'm sure it's a good thing!

668
00:34:55,934 --> 00:34:56,934
(Her reaction is broken.)

669
00:34:56,959 --> 00:34:59,325
What does that mean? Why
does she keep doing that?

670
00:35:00,035 --> 00:35:02,044
- Did you get a ton of coins?
- No!

671
00:35:02,069 --> 00:35:04,822
Did you get all the votes?
I think she got about three.

672
00:35:06,683 --> 00:35:09,557
Oh, she's kicking her legs.
She's happy. They're floating.

673
00:35:11,171 --> 00:35:13,132
- Now it's Yeo-min's turn.
- Yeo-min.

674
00:35:13,157 --> 00:35:14,428
(Nervous)

675
00:35:14,453 --> 00:35:15,709
I have no idea.

676
00:35:17,614 --> 00:35:21,687
(Will she get a coin from
Won-jae, her first date?)

677
00:35:21,712 --> 00:35:24,754
(Or from her dinner date Ji-min?)

678
00:35:26,172 --> 00:35:28,817
- I think she got two votes.
- I think so, too.

679
00:35:30,756 --> 00:35:32,081
At least one, please...

680
00:35:33,389 --> 00:35:34,616
(Peek)

681
00:35:34,641 --> 00:35:37,699
(Lee Yeo-min: 1 Vote)

682
00:35:37,724 --> 00:35:38,851
Gosh, that scared me!

683
00:35:38,876 --> 00:35:41,092
Won-jae didn't get mad at her, did he?

684
00:35:42,237 --> 00:35:43,531
Because she didn't choose him?

685
00:35:43,556 --> 00:35:46,881
He even came on "Steel Troops."
I don't think he's that kind of guy.

686
00:35:48,751 --> 00:35:50,481
(Flop)

687
00:35:52,013 --> 00:35:55,255
(Either Ji-min or Won-jae
didn't give her a coin.)

688
00:35:55,489 --> 00:35:57,569
Yeo-min looks like she
has a lot on her mind.

689
00:35:57,839 --> 00:35:59,261
No, I'm fine.

690
00:36:00,502 --> 00:36:01,502
I'm a bit...

691
00:36:01,906 --> 00:36:03,224
(Curious)

692
00:36:04,141 --> 00:36:05,451
I'll have to wait and see.

693
00:36:06,046 --> 00:36:07,548
I wonder what that means.

694
00:36:08,884 --> 00:36:11,289
(Bounce, bounce, bounce)

695
00:36:11,313 --> 00:36:13,473
- It's Ji-min.
- Why is she so cute?

696
00:36:14,695 --> 00:36:17,915
(Ji-min is going to check her locker.)

697
00:36:18,967 --> 00:36:21,237
I thought I'd get zero coins.

698
00:36:22,376 --> 00:36:24,162
Oh no. She has no confidence.

699
00:36:24,187 --> 00:36:27,512
(No one came to get her in the morning.)

700
00:36:28,741 --> 00:36:33,305
(During the dinner date,
she had many rivals.)

701
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,515
(It wasn't an easy day...
Did she really get 0 votes?)

702
00:36:36,540 --> 00:36:38,970
- Please let there be a coin.
- I think there will be one.

703
00:36:38,995 --> 00:36:40,448
(Please! Just one!)

704
00:36:41,054 --> 00:36:43,902
(What are the results?)

705
00:36:44,660 --> 00:36:45,727
Did she get any?

706
00:36:46,191 --> 00:36:48,574
(Yang Ji-min: 1 Vote)

707
00:36:48,599 --> 00:36:50,633
(There's a coin!)

708
00:36:51,412 --> 00:36:54,501
- I'm thrilled like it happened to me!
What a relief. - I'm so happy!

709
00:36:54,526 --> 00:36:55,924
I wonder who gave it to her.

710
00:36:56,951 --> 00:36:58,261
I have no idea.

711
00:36:58,598 --> 00:37:00,422
Ji-min... No, I don't
think it was him.

712
00:37:00,447 --> 00:37:04,496
It seemed like he was more
interested in Yeo-min and Ha-neul.

713
00:37:04,521 --> 00:37:06,308
It just felt that way.

714
00:37:06,986 --> 00:37:08,453
Oh, she felt that way.

715
00:37:09,021 --> 00:37:12,378
Then I guess Ha-neul will get two coins.

716
00:37:13,644 --> 00:37:16,088
(Ha-neul is going to check her locker.)

717
00:37:16,113 --> 00:37:20,519
I had a big feeling I might get zero coins.

718
00:37:22,339 --> 00:37:24,184
(Ha-neul checks carefully.)

719
00:37:24,876 --> 00:37:29,122
(Lee Ha-neul: 2 Votes)

720
00:37:29,980 --> 00:37:33,146
- I guess she didn't expect to
receive two of them. - Yeah.

721
00:37:33,171 --> 00:37:35,625
- They're from Su-won and Ji-min, right?
- Most likely.

722
00:37:36,811 --> 00:37:38,077
I wonder who it is.

723
00:37:38,996 --> 00:37:39,996
What's this?

724
00:37:40,864 --> 00:37:43,675
- You got a lot of coins, didn't you?
- No. Nope.

725
00:37:45,551 --> 00:37:50,202
I think one of the coins are from Su-won.

726
00:37:50,763 --> 00:37:54,160
I really can't tell who could've
given me the other one.

727
00:37:54,561 --> 00:37:55,823
- Really?
- Seriously?

728
00:37:56,053 --> 00:37:58,029
- How could she not know?
- Ji-min tried so hard.

729
00:37:58,054 --> 00:38:00,231
But she was too busy
being conscious of Su-won.

730
00:38:00,566 --> 00:38:03,590
- She was too conscious of him.
- So she didn't notice Ji-min's feelings.

731
00:38:03,776 --> 00:38:06,180
(Jae-hyung is checking his locker.)

732
00:38:06,205 --> 00:38:08,684
I don't express my
interest in someone first.

733
00:38:08,933 --> 00:38:11,084
Most of the time, the
woman liked me first.

734
00:38:12,523 --> 00:38:13,857
He was always alone.

735
00:38:16,071 --> 00:38:17,383
Gosh, I'm embarrassed.

736
00:38:20,061 --> 00:38:21,719
He laughed a lot today.

737
00:38:25,417 --> 00:38:27,799
(How many coins did Jae-hyung get?)

738
00:38:27,824 --> 00:38:29,380
I don't think he expects any.

739
00:38:31,439 --> 00:38:34,180
(Seo Jae-hyung: 0 Votes)

740
00:38:35,406 --> 00:38:37,144
(Jae-hyung, we're rooting
for you./Sincere.)

741
00:38:37,169 --> 00:38:38,781
We don't know anything yet.

742
00:38:38,806 --> 00:38:41,265
- It's just the first day.
- It's just the beginning.

743
00:38:42,621 --> 00:38:45,689
(Jae-hyung is quiet. Is he hurt?)

744
00:38:47,649 --> 00:38:49,768
I don't waver because I got zero coins.

745
00:38:50,787 --> 00:38:51,787
As expected.

746
00:38:52,681 --> 00:38:54,613
(Won-jae is here to check his locker.)

747
00:38:54,638 --> 00:38:56,647
- Won-jae.
- Won-jae.

748
00:38:57,595 --> 00:38:59,246
I predict I'll get one coin.

749
00:38:59,932 --> 00:39:02,226
- I kind of anticipated it.
- Really?

750
00:39:02,482 --> 00:39:04,085
I thought, "Won't he come?"

751
00:39:04,652 --> 00:39:08,175
I hope it's from Yeo-min.

752
00:39:12,736 --> 00:39:15,967
(Kang Won-jae: 1 Vote)

753
00:39:15,992 --> 00:39:19,050
- Yeo-min?
- It's probably from her, right?

754
00:39:21,382 --> 00:39:22,874
(Satisfied)

755
00:39:23,262 --> 00:39:24,262
He's happy.

756
00:39:26,515 --> 00:39:28,140
(Won-jae tries to
keep a straight face.)

757
00:39:28,165 --> 00:39:29,674
(Stare)

758
00:39:31,630 --> 00:39:33,226
I can't control my expression.

759
00:39:33,251 --> 00:39:35,718
You don't know what to do, right?

760
00:39:35,743 --> 00:39:38,412
- I have no idea.
- I don't know what to do.

761
00:39:40,797 --> 00:39:42,720
- He'll get one vote, right?
- Jung-woo.

762
00:39:43,132 --> 00:39:44,559
I only wanted one from In-seong.

763
00:39:45,289 --> 00:39:47,423
It feels like there's a
light coming from there.

764
00:39:48,824 --> 00:39:50,086
There should be a coin.

765
00:39:50,650 --> 00:39:51,945
Gosh, I'm nervous.

766
00:39:51,970 --> 00:39:54,074
(Yoon Jung-woo: 1 Vote)

767
00:39:59,994 --> 00:40:00,994
Oh dear.

768
00:40:01,755 --> 00:40:02,948
He's looking at everyone.

769
00:40:03,263 --> 00:40:06,570
Did you realize that we're all
self-conscious of Jae-hyung?

770
00:40:07,216 --> 00:40:09,890
We usually laugh, but when
he appears, we turn all serious.

771
00:40:10,024 --> 00:40:11,210
"Can we laugh?"

772
00:40:12,890 --> 00:40:15,992
(Su-won is going to check his locker.)

773
00:40:16,017 --> 00:40:19,599
I gave my coin to Ha-neul.

774
00:40:22,217 --> 00:40:23,907
I didn't expect this would happen.

775
00:40:24,933 --> 00:40:28,490
I think he'll be very nervous
because they didn't eat together.

776
00:40:29,612 --> 00:40:32,715
I don't know if she changed her mind.

777
00:40:33,546 --> 00:40:37,038
(Did Su-won get a coin?)

778
00:40:38,070 --> 00:40:39,438
(Shaking pupils)

779
00:40:40,144 --> 00:40:41,931
I have no clue from his expression.

780
00:40:46,139 --> 00:40:47,139
Are there none?

781
00:40:47,164 --> 00:40:48,662
(What does that nod mean?)

782
00:40:50,063 --> 00:40:51,254
Aww, come on!

783
00:40:52,596 --> 00:40:54,129
His pupils are shaking.

784
00:40:54,685 --> 00:40:55,685
(Nod)

785
00:40:57,007 --> 00:40:58,074
What's going on?

786
00:40:59,952 --> 00:41:02,278
(Curious 1 & 2)

787
00:41:02,818 --> 00:41:03,885
You look bright.

788
00:41:04,284 --> 00:41:06,300
What? No.
I don't know.

789
00:41:09,814 --> 00:41:11,053
Your face turned red.

790
00:41:12,521 --> 00:41:14,101
I don't know.
I have no clue.

791
00:41:16,392 --> 00:41:17,717
Did he get two coins?

792
00:41:18,021 --> 00:41:20,228
Is that why he looked around?

793
00:41:20,253 --> 00:41:22,786
(Su-won's expression is hard to read.)

794
00:41:23,696 --> 00:41:26,837
(Ji-min is the last one to go.)

795
00:41:26,862 --> 00:41:28,379
The winner of the dinner date.

796
00:41:28,804 --> 00:41:30,327
He's today's Mr. Popular.

797
00:41:30,352 --> 00:41:32,432
(His footsteps are kind
of filled with excitement.)

798
00:41:35,852 --> 00:41:37,057
Three women chose me.

799
00:41:37,375 --> 00:41:40,091
I realized this is what it means
to be full even if you don't eat.

800
00:41:41,173 --> 00:41:42,506
I wonder what's in there.

801
00:41:42,531 --> 00:41:45,032
(Did his popularity during the
dinner pay off as Love Coins?)

802
00:41:45,567 --> 00:41:48,860
(How many coins did Ji-min get?)

803
00:41:49,633 --> 00:41:50,887
What's that look on his face?

804
00:41:50,912 --> 00:41:52,881
- I haven't the faintest idea!
- I can't tell.

805
00:41:52,906 --> 00:41:55,375
Why did he check on his tippy toes?

806
00:42:00,265 --> 00:42:02,106
Gosh, I don't know.

807
00:42:02,926 --> 00:42:04,743
- He said he doesn't know.
- What's happening?

808
00:42:04,768 --> 00:42:06,021
Did he get zero coins?

809
00:42:06,046 --> 00:42:07,793
(The men are done
checking their lockers.)

810
00:42:08,718 --> 00:42:10,226
Your reaction is lukewarm.

811
00:42:12,143 --> 00:42:13,618
(A natural sigh)

812
00:42:13,643 --> 00:42:16,453
- Doesn't he look like he
has a lot on his mind? - Yes.

813
00:42:18,834 --> 00:42:22,386
(What are their results?)

814
00:42:24,157 --> 00:42:26,987
(Jung Su-won: 1 Vote
Ahn Ji-min: 1 Vote)

815
00:42:27,150 --> 00:42:28,808
They each got one vote.

816
00:42:28,833 --> 00:42:30,421
But what's with their expressions?

817
00:42:30,619 --> 00:42:32,456
Why did Ji-min say he doesn't know?

818
00:42:32,481 --> 00:42:34,426
Maybe he assumed he'd get at least two.

819
00:42:34,451 --> 00:42:36,563
Since three people went on a date with him.

820
00:42:36,588 --> 00:42:38,517
- Right. - "Which two didn't
give me a coin?"

821
00:42:38,789 --> 00:42:41,289
- He could've thought that, right?
- It's possible.

822
00:42:41,314 --> 00:42:44,099
And Su-won could've
thought, "Did Ha-neul really give

823
00:42:44,124 --> 00:42:46,960
it to me? Why? She didn't
pick me for the dinner date."

824
00:42:49,342 --> 00:42:52,174
Wow, this is interesting. It's intriguing.

825
00:42:52,924 --> 00:42:54,583
- It's interesting?
- Yeah.

826
00:42:54,608 --> 00:42:55,656
Did you see something?

827
00:42:55,681 --> 00:42:56,681
I have a question.

828
00:42:57,603 --> 00:43:00,096
When you opened the girls'
locker, did they already have one?

829
00:43:00,121 --> 00:43:01,121
(Perk)

830
00:43:03,451 --> 00:43:05,576
- That's why you said it was interesting.
- I see.

831
00:43:05,731 --> 00:43:06,969
- Is it unexpected?
- Yes.

832
00:43:06,994 --> 00:43:09,415
- It is?
- Yes, more than I thought.

833
00:43:10,173 --> 00:43:11,173
Really?

834
00:43:11,460 --> 00:43:13,277
- I'm curious.
- It's unexpected.

835
00:43:14,598 --> 00:43:17,557
- Does Jae-hyung know?
- He knows?

836
00:43:17,799 --> 00:43:22,866
When the guys opened the locker, I'm sure
some of them saw a coin already in there.

837
00:43:23,535 --> 00:43:24,535
But why did Jae-hyung...?

838
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:26,433
(Only one person got two coins today.)

839
00:43:26,458 --> 00:43:28,038
Or did he give Ha-neul one?

840
00:43:28,374 --> 00:43:30,230
- Maybe!
- Jae-hyung gave her a coin?

841
00:43:30,699 --> 00:43:32,407
Do one of those coins belong to him?

842
00:43:33,815 --> 00:43:35,981
- How does it feel?
- So-so.

843
00:43:36,006 --> 00:43:37,073
- So-so?
- Yes.

844
00:43:37,256 --> 00:43:38,796
- Everyone's just so-so.
- Yeah.

845
00:43:39,101 --> 00:43:41,362
None of us were able to
address them casually, right?

846
00:43:41,387 --> 00:43:42,387
Yeah.

847
00:43:42,833 --> 00:43:46,437
Oh, I did. I addressed
Jung-woo casually.

848
00:43:46,643 --> 00:43:47,643
Oh my!

849
00:43:48,591 --> 00:43:50,059
- With Jung-woo?
- Jung-woo?

850
00:43:50,084 --> 00:43:51,084
"Jung-woo."

851
00:43:53,870 --> 00:43:55,511
(She kicks her foot
out of embarrassment.)

852
00:43:56,361 --> 00:43:58,371
(Hahahahaha!)

853
00:43:59,747 --> 00:44:01,547
They got pretty close, too.

854
00:44:01,766 --> 00:44:05,067
What was that?

855
00:44:05,380 --> 00:44:07,285
What's that? What's that?

856
00:44:07,765 --> 00:44:09,351
Something appeared on the screen!

857
00:44:09,598 --> 00:44:10,741
(Startled)

858
00:44:11,284 --> 00:44:13,911
She got caught off guard because
she was thinking of Jung-woo!

859
00:44:14,554 --> 00:44:16,860
(The screen turns on
in the men's room, too.)

860
00:44:16,885 --> 00:44:18,149
Something popped up.

861
00:44:18,174 --> 00:44:19,497
(What is it?)

862
00:44:22,844 --> 00:44:24,339
- What's that?
- What is it?

863
00:44:24,474 --> 00:44:26,874
Oh, I think it's a surveillance camera.

864
00:44:28,065 --> 00:44:29,331
A surveillance camera?

865
00:44:30,909 --> 00:44:32,186
Why did they turn it on?

866
00:44:32,752 --> 00:44:34,418
It looks like a scene
from a horror movie.

867
00:44:34,443 --> 00:44:35,966
What's going on? Why is it so...?

868
00:44:37,359 --> 00:44:39,559
- What is it?
- What's going on?

869
00:44:44,772 --> 00:44:48,168
(A silhouette appears in the darkness.)

870
00:44:48,522 --> 00:44:49,569
Is it a woman?

871
00:44:49,594 --> 00:44:51,077
With a suitcase?

872
00:44:51,913 --> 00:44:53,144
I got goosebumps!

873
00:44:54,694 --> 00:44:56,131
No way!

874
00:44:56,608 --> 00:44:58,117
There's another girl! She's here!

875
00:44:58,524 --> 00:45:00,556
She's here! She's here!

876
00:45:00,916 --> 00:45:02,383
I just got the chills.

877
00:45:03,492 --> 00:45:06,959
(A mysterious woman appears
when everyone has let their guard down.)

878
00:45:07,738 --> 00:45:10,050
(Even though they see
it, they can't believe it.)

879
00:45:10,847 --> 00:45:11,847
What's happening?

880
00:45:14,763 --> 00:45:17,336
(Another participant has
come to the Love Mansion.)

881
00:45:20,814 --> 00:45:23,898
(The women's room is
swept up in shock and horror.)

882
00:45:23,923 --> 00:45:24,996
(Goosebumps)

883
00:45:25,021 --> 00:45:26,480
Wow, I can't believe this.

884
00:45:26,505 --> 00:45:29,054
Wow, this is crazy. I
really got goosebumps.

885
00:45:29,079 --> 00:45:30,079
Seriously.

886
00:45:30,104 --> 00:45:32,390
- I really got the chills.
- So did I.

887
00:45:33,260 --> 00:45:36,220
The happiest person right now is Jae-hyung.

888
00:45:36,556 --> 00:45:38,602
- He has hope!
- Yup!

889
00:45:38,997 --> 00:45:40,736
I wondered why they
were showing us this.

890
00:45:40,761 --> 00:45:43,133
- This is awesome.
- My spirits suddenly went up.

891
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:46,360
- Bingo.
- I knew it.

892
00:45:46,749 --> 00:45:48,622
- Bingo.
- Way to go, Jae-hyung!

893
00:45:48,801 --> 00:45:50,460
My spirits suddenly went up.

894
00:45:51,429 --> 00:45:52,429
Same here!

895
00:45:52,810 --> 00:45:55,350
Me, too! I'm on cloud nine!

896
00:45:55,375 --> 00:45:57,402
It might be a war, but let's do our best.

897
00:45:59,396 --> 00:46:02,471
(The new participant is
already in front of the door.)

898
00:46:02,496 --> 00:46:05,084
Her outfit is entirely black.
She gives off the vibes of...

899
00:46:05,109 --> 00:46:07,325
She kind of has chic vibes.

900
00:46:17,312 --> 00:46:18,820
(Glance)

901
00:46:21,127 --> 00:46:22,508
(Eyes wide open)

902
00:46:28,308 --> 00:46:31,350
(The new housemate of the Love
Mansion whose graceful aura is charming.)

903
00:46:31,480 --> 00:46:33,075
- She's gorgeous.
- She's dazzling.

904
00:46:33,100 --> 00:46:36,291
She doesn't look like
any of the other women.

905
00:46:36,316 --> 00:46:38,849
Right. They all have different styles.

906
00:46:39,155 --> 00:46:40,512
She has different charms.

907
00:46:40,537 --> 00:46:43,568
(What kind of time will she
have at the Love Mansion?)

908
00:46:43,593 --> 00:46:46,000
- We should warmly welcome her.
- Of course!

909
00:46:46,025 --> 00:46:47,281
Something else popped up.

910
00:46:47,306 --> 00:46:49,592
- I guess we have to go there.
- Us?

911
00:46:50,361 --> 00:46:53,301
(The final participant is
sitting at the table by herself.)

912
00:46:53,421 --> 00:46:55,026
We're coming. We're coming over there.

913
00:46:55,664 --> 00:46:57,466
Let me check the mirror once.

914
00:46:57,857 --> 00:47:01,230
Ji-min, aren't you acting
differently from before?

915
00:47:01,464 --> 00:47:03,297
I need to brush my teeth.

916
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:05,768
Why? For what?

917
00:47:06,978 --> 00:47:10,613
- Oh my gosh!
- This is so much fun!

918
00:47:12,755 --> 00:47:14,937
- Hello!
- Hello.

919
00:47:14,962 --> 00:47:17,484
(The women arrived
at the living room first.)

920
00:47:17,949 --> 00:47:22,425
- It's nice to meet you.
- Hello.

921
00:47:22,450 --> 00:47:25,827
- Where should we sit?
- Sit here.

922
00:47:26,426 --> 00:47:29,921
- Hello.
- Hi.

923
00:47:36,993 --> 00:47:38,128
(Swish)

924
00:47:39,620 --> 00:47:42,394
(The men arrive in
the living room, too.)

925
00:47:42,419 --> 00:47:44,848
- Hello.
- Hello.

926
00:47:45,709 --> 00:47:47,447
Hello.

927
00:47:49,178 --> 00:47:50,433
(Glance)

928
00:47:51,627 --> 00:47:53,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

929
00:47:54,449 --> 00:47:56,068
They all fixed themselves up.

930
00:47:56,093 --> 00:47:58,951
(Their expressions are kind of
glowing because of the new encounter.)

931
00:48:01,431 --> 00:48:03,558
(Crowded)

932
00:48:08,321 --> 00:48:10,622
When I first saw her, I
noticed she looked graceful.

933
00:48:11,595 --> 00:48:14,515
All the possibilities are open.
It's officially the beginning.

934
00:48:14,741 --> 00:48:19,768
She's the closest to my ideal
type. So I was honestly surprised.

935
00:48:20,149 --> 00:48:21,506
Really?

936
00:48:22,382 --> 00:48:24,391
Her first impression wasn't bad.

937
00:48:24,416 --> 00:48:26,323
Wow, even Su-won?

938
00:48:26,348 --> 00:48:29,777
Isn't this the perfect time to
receive the spotlight? Right?

939
00:48:29,802 --> 00:48:30,802
Yes.

940
00:48:31,589 --> 00:48:33,541
Wow, a strong rival has appeared.

941
00:48:34,404 --> 00:48:35,470
This is awesome.

942
00:48:35,495 --> 00:48:37,238
(Jung-woo is the last to arrive.)

943
00:48:37,754 --> 00:48:39,095
(Glance)

944
00:48:40,133 --> 00:48:41,545
Sit here, Jung-woo.

945
00:48:42,460 --> 00:48:44,396
(She carefully looks at Jung-woo.)

946
00:48:48,012 --> 00:48:50,902
(She avoids making eye contact
with Jung-woo, who sits in front of her.)

947
00:48:51,220 --> 00:48:52,993
- Hello.
- Hi.

948
00:48:54,918 --> 00:48:56,831
- Hello.
- Hi.

949
00:49:01,283 --> 00:49:05,185
The new girl happens
to have prominent cheekbones.

950
00:49:05,654 --> 00:49:07,476
(Do-yeon is very keen!)

951
00:49:07,666 --> 00:49:10,836
- Jung-woo will keep a good eye on her.
- You crack me up! Oh my god.

952
00:49:11,702 --> 00:49:15,904
(The living room fills
with awkward silence.)

953
00:49:16,417 --> 00:49:18,814
- What did you take here?
- A cab.

954
00:49:20,358 --> 00:49:21,558
Where do you live?

955
00:49:21,747 --> 00:49:24,001
Oh, I live in Samseong-dong.

956
00:49:27,152 --> 00:49:31,873
My name is Jung
Da-Na. I'm 28 years old.

957
00:49:34,482 --> 00:49:35,562
(Smile)

958
00:49:36,876 --> 00:49:38,247
(Hmm...)

959
00:49:39,878 --> 00:49:41,450
I work for a clothing company.

960
00:49:43,739 --> 00:49:46,445
(Focused)

961
00:49:48,125 --> 00:49:49,125
I'm Jung Da-Na.

962
00:49:49,150 --> 00:49:53,039
(The last participant of
"Love Catcher": Jung Da-Na)

963
00:49:57,451 --> 00:49:59,704
(What's going on?)

964
00:50:00,083 --> 00:50:02,837
I always get nervous
when that screen appears.

965
00:50:06,794 --> 00:50:08,771
(Out of the 10 participants...)

966
00:50:12,235 --> 00:50:15,928
(there are Money
Catchers with fake identities.)

967
00:50:16,096 --> 00:50:19,599
(The time has finally come!)

968
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:21,444
- What?
- Huh?

969
00:50:22,224 --> 00:50:23,753
(Confused)

970
00:50:25,585 --> 00:50:27,640
(Shaking pupils)

971
00:50:27,665 --> 00:50:30,262
Out of all 10 of us, right?

972
00:50:30,287 --> 00:50:33,503
- That means their profiles
are lies, right? - Yes.

973
00:50:34,032 --> 00:50:36,849
- But we don't know how many
there are, right? - There's one. Right?

974
00:50:36,874 --> 00:50:39,891
They didn't tell us the number.

975
00:50:40,133 --> 00:50:42,283
So I don't think there's just one.

976
00:50:47,330 --> 00:50:49,695
There could be just one,
or there could be more.

977
00:50:50,326 --> 00:50:52,254
This is getting really interesting.

978
00:50:53,918 --> 00:50:58,235
I thought about what I
would do if I were there.

979
00:50:58,260 --> 00:51:00,906
I think I would've pretended
not to understand that rule.

980
00:51:00,931 --> 00:51:07,966
In that means, Ha-neul looks
really shocked and flustered.

981
00:51:08,455 --> 00:51:09,455
- Like this.
- Right.

982
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:11,180
What do you think about Da-Na?

983
00:51:11,205 --> 00:51:15,007
First off, the men all seem into her.

984
00:51:15,039 --> 00:51:17,502
- She's become the center of attention.
- Precisely.

985
00:51:17,527 --> 00:51:20,251
Now it's time to answer today's question.

986
00:51:20,349 --> 00:51:22,048
Time goes my really quickly.

987
00:51:22,073 --> 00:51:25,804
Which Money Catcher
is hiding their identity?

988
00:51:25,943 --> 00:51:28,451
I pick Su-won.

989
00:51:29,034 --> 00:51:32,710
I thought he was just straightforward,
but after thinking that he

990
00:51:32,735 --> 00:51:36,411
could be a Money Catcher, I
realized it could just be his concept.

991
00:51:36,436 --> 00:51:38,398
- His actions.
- Yes, it all fits.

992
00:51:39,155 --> 00:51:40,155
Then I'll go with...

993
00:51:40,814 --> 00:51:42,414
- In-seong?
- In-seong?

994
00:51:42,962 --> 00:51:46,171
I feel like she's not a student
but someone with a job.

995
00:51:46,196 --> 00:51:48,401
- Oh, I see.
- Same here.

996
00:51:48,627 --> 00:51:50,777
I think she lied about her age, too.

997
00:51:50,936 --> 00:51:52,602
Oh, so she could be older?

998
00:51:52,627 --> 00:51:55,304
She brought a lot of medicine, too!

999
00:51:56,109 --> 00:51:57,497
Are you doubtful of her health?

1000
00:51:57,522 --> 00:52:00,357
A 26-year-old would not
pack medicine like that.

1001
00:52:00,390 --> 00:52:02,955
He's got a point. It's all from experience.

1002
00:52:02,980 --> 00:52:07,817
- I pick In-seong today.
- Two people already picked her.

1003
00:52:08,957 --> 00:52:10,157
That's unexpected.

1004
00:52:10,539 --> 00:52:14,427
Her reactions make me
think she's a Money Catcher.

1005
00:52:14,622 --> 00:52:21,021
I keep suspecting Yeo-min.
She doesn't really show her emotions.

1006
00:52:21,246 --> 00:52:22,254
Right, I agree.

1007
00:52:22,279 --> 00:52:25,155
And during the dinner date, she
didn't seem interested in Ji-min.

1008
00:52:25,180 --> 00:52:26,441
That's what I thought, too!

1009
00:52:26,466 --> 00:52:28,165
She was just eating
the Mille-Feuille Nabe.

1010
00:52:28,190 --> 00:52:31,008
She was just enjoying the food.

1011
00:52:32,324 --> 00:52:35,299
Did you pick, Ho-jun? Will
we be able to hear it today?

1012
00:52:35,819 --> 00:52:37,573
- I did choose.
- I'd like to go home.

1013
00:52:37,598 --> 00:52:40,090
But after hearing everyone's
answers, I'm very confused.

1014
00:52:40,237 --> 00:52:42,665
I'll go with my guts and pick Ha-neul.

1015
00:52:43,835 --> 00:52:46,152
- Why? - I think she works in broadcasting

1016
00:52:46,177 --> 00:52:49,846
but lied that she
just opened a restaurant.

1017
00:52:50,350 --> 00:52:54,286
She first got to know Su-won,
but she chose Ji-min later.

1018
00:52:54,311 --> 00:52:59,076
- Right. - She's trying to figure
out who is here for love or money

1019
00:52:59,502 --> 00:53:02,875
before making her choice. I saw
that kind of carefulness from her.

1020
00:53:03,649 --> 00:53:08,173
In-seong got two votes. Su-won,
Ha-neul, and Yeo-min each got one vote.

1021
00:53:08,401 --> 00:53:11,100
- We did come up with different answers.
- Right.

1022
00:53:11,125 --> 00:53:15,150
If it's not one of them, it
will be pretty embarrassing.

1023
00:53:15,987 --> 00:53:17,615
- Who is it?
- I'm curious.

1024
00:53:20,068 --> 00:53:23,261
(Revealing the Money Catcher
who made a fake identity)

1025
00:53:23,286 --> 00:53:25,963
- So the person's...
- Real career!

1026
00:53:26,140 --> 00:53:27,608
I can't watch!

1027
00:53:28,770 --> 00:53:31,572
(The Money Catcher's
car smoothly glides in.)

1028
00:53:31,597 --> 00:53:33,488
- What?
- What's that?

1029
00:53:34,691 --> 00:53:36,091
It's one of the guys.

1030
00:53:36,992 --> 00:53:39,176
- Isn't that a Porsche?
- It's a Porsche!

1031
00:53:40,155 --> 00:53:42,211
- Is that Su-won?
- No, it's Ji-min!

1032
00:53:42,236 --> 00:53:44,055
You know why? He lied
about not having a car!

1033
00:53:44,262 --> 00:53:46,023
Oops, I'm sorry for speaking informally.

1034
00:53:46,048 --> 00:53:49,250
It's definitely a guy. Hang on.
Su-won is the only guy we picked!

1035
00:53:49,419 --> 00:53:50,419
That's true.

1036
00:53:50,665 --> 00:53:53,324
Then is it Yang Ji-min?

1037
00:53:54,908 --> 00:53:56,543
- It's possible.
- She suddenly goes...

1038
00:54:01,313 --> 00:54:02,987
- It's a guy.
- It's a guy.

1039
00:54:05,207 --> 00:54:08,015
(One man hid his identity.)

1040
00:54:08,040 --> 00:54:09,868
I'm dying of curiosity!

1041
00:54:09,893 --> 00:54:13,635
(The man who is tricking everyone is...)

1042
00:54:13,660 --> 00:54:15,080
(Hurry up and show us!)

1043
00:54:15,105 --> 00:54:16,667
What? Who is it? Who is it?

1044
00:54:18,036 --> 00:54:22,022
(The one who changed his
identity is Yoon Jung-woo.)

1045
00:54:22,973 --> 00:54:25,649
I'm actually 32-year-old
Yoon Jung-woo who

1046
00:54:25,935 --> 00:54:28,425
is the CEO of a start-up
consulting company.

1047
00:54:28,971 --> 00:54:31,319
- It's Jung-woo!
- Ugh, I should've chosen him!

1048
00:54:31,798 --> 00:54:33,044
(Late regret)

1049
00:54:33,069 --> 00:54:34,695
- What?
- None of us got it right.

1050
00:54:34,720 --> 00:54:35,720
No one picked him.

1051
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:40,669
I have two offices. One in
Hanam and one in Suwon.

1052
00:54:41,101 --> 00:54:43,530
And I have over 20 employees.

1053
00:54:45,051 --> 00:54:47,765
Right now, I'm doing consulting.

1054
00:54:48,158 --> 00:54:49,855
I link companies to subcontractors

1055
00:54:50,280 --> 00:54:54,436
and create business plans for
those who can't do it themselves.

1056
00:54:54,626 --> 00:54:57,693
With interior design,
we do branding

1057
00:54:58,040 --> 00:55:01,921
and also give advice on
what image would be better.

1058
00:55:04,207 --> 00:55:07,047
I lied about my job because

1059
00:55:07,350 --> 00:55:10,095
as an entrepreneur, there
are times when I have economic

1060
00:55:10,120 --> 00:55:12,438
freedom and times when
I experience difficulties.

1061
00:55:15,743 --> 00:55:20,067
When I'm doing well
financially, dating goes well, too.

1062
00:55:20,422 --> 00:55:25,575
But when I experience financial
troubles, the one I love tends to leave me.

1063
00:55:25,863 --> 00:55:28,284
I also get hurt over small words.

1064
00:55:29,032 --> 00:55:31,850
So in a situation when
I'm financially well-off,

1065
00:55:32,375 --> 00:55:34,496
I can't really trust
people who approach me.

1066
00:55:38,758 --> 00:55:42,194
So if I have a chance to meet someone new,

1067
00:55:44,003 --> 00:55:48,655
I will say that my job is a
freelance travel writer, which

1068
00:55:49,243 --> 00:55:53,515
was my dream job, instead of
a CEO in order to find true love.

1069
00:55:54,903 --> 00:55:56,807
But why is he a Money Catcher?

1070
00:55:57,776 --> 00:56:02,716
If I find true love, I'll
change my identity.

1071
00:56:04,388 --> 00:56:08,229
I think there's a chance
I'll be able to do that.

1072
00:56:10,409 --> 00:56:12,974
In order to find someone
who sincerely loves me,

1073
00:56:14,304 --> 00:56:19,296
I lied about my job and joined
the program as a Money Catcher.

1074
00:56:21,302 --> 00:56:24,263
(Will Jung-woo be able to find true love?)

1075
00:56:24,633 --> 00:56:28,259
(Identity Reveal:
Yoon Jung-woo = Money Catcher)

1076
00:56:29,097 --> 00:56:34,804
So if you look at it, Jung-woo might be
the one with the most open mind here.

1077
00:56:34,829 --> 00:56:37,016
He could be the real, honest Love Catcher.

1078
00:56:37,041 --> 00:56:38,773
- If you look at it in another way.
- Yeah.

1079
00:56:38,798 --> 00:56:44,548
We'll have to keep an eye on whether
Jung-woo will find true love or not.

1080
00:56:44,573 --> 00:56:45,573
Yes, that's right.

1081
00:56:46,179 --> 00:56:48,219
The important thing is
that none of us got it right.

1082
00:56:49,420 --> 00:56:53,166
- Let's work harder, you guys.
- It's just the beginning.

1083
00:56:56,308 --> 00:56:59,324
- She looks like a model.
- She's so ladylike.

1084
00:56:59,357 --> 00:57:02,957
- She's so attractive.
- She came to shake things up!

1085
00:57:05,334 --> 00:57:10,214
When you saw the guys for the first time,
is there someone who caught your eye?

1086
00:57:11,069 --> 00:57:12,475
Today is our challenge, right?

1087
00:57:12,755 --> 00:57:14,207
I love this person.

1088
00:57:15,694 --> 00:57:17,487
- Are you looking at my lips?
- Yes.

1089
00:57:19,498 --> 00:57:22,078
- What's on your mind?
- I don't know.

1090
00:57:22,455 --> 00:57:26,471
Are you still stuck between the two
guys you mentioned in the beginning?

1091
00:57:27,627 --> 00:57:30,611
Gosh. What should I do?

1092
00:57:30,636 --> 00:57:35,685
Is there someone you're interested in?

1093
00:57:37,265 --> 00:57:38,265
Really?

1094
00:57:38,742 --> 00:57:40,107
I'm definitely certain.

1095
00:57:41,174 --> 00:57:43,943
Who is it? I'm so curious!

1096
00:57:45,805 --> 00:57:48,535
Whenever we meet, I feel
like I'm facing my ideal type.

1097
00:57:48,967 --> 00:57:51,578
My heart fluttered a lot.
